One of the most provocative claims that the intense reports on the process, including the extensive use of Twitter by mass media journalists, created "a circus atmosphere," and such widespread and immediate saturation with exalting details made public passions an inappropriate influence on the jury.
The complaint could force the judges of appeal to deal with the question of whether the new technology requires new rules in the court room.
