The WikiLeaks case has a double value.
On the one hand, it reveals an apparent scandal, a scandal that only seems to be a scandal in the light of the hypocrisy that governs relations between States, citizens and the press.
On the other hand, it announces profound changes at international level and anticipates a future dominated by regression.
But let's go step by step.
The first aspect of WikiLeaks is the confirmation of the fact that every file created by a secret service (regardless of the nation to which it belongs) is made up exclusively of press cuts.
