But it is also clear that, with current technologies, it is not possible to expect to have confidential conversations over the telephone.
Nothing is easier than finding out whether and when a Head of State has moved by plane and contacted one of the counterparts.
How can they maintain private and confidential relations in the future?
I know perfectly well that, for the moment, my foresight is a matter of science fiction and, therefore, novelesque, but I imagine government agents who move discreetly in proceedings with uncontrollable itineraries, carrying messages that have been learned by memory or, at most, hiding some data written in the heels of their shoes.
